TITLE: Executing Fill Order Transaction (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to execute the fill order transaction on-chain using an ethers.js signer instance. It sends a transaction to the limit order contract with the encoded data as the calldata. The `maxFeePerGas` and `maxPriorityFeePerGas` parameters are also specified to control gas fees.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/limit-order/developer-guides/fill-limit-order.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const fillOrderTx = await signer.sendTransaction({
    data: data.data.encodedData,
    to: limitOrderContract,
    from: signerAddress,
    maxFeePerGas: 100000000000,
    maxPriorityFeePerGas: 100000000000
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Specifying Limit Order Parameters in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Creates a request body object with the necessary parameters for a limit order, including chain ID, asset addresses, amounts, and expiration time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/limit-order/developer-guides/create-limit-order.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const requestBody: CreateOrderUnsignedBody = {
    chainId: ChainId.MATIC.toString(),
    makerAsset: makerAsset.address, // USDC
    takerAsset: takerAsset.address, // KNC
    maker: signerAddress,
    allowedSenders: [signerAddress], // Included so that only our account can fill this order
    makingAmount: "10000", // 0.01 USDC
    takingAmount: "20000000000000000", // 0.02 KNC
    expiredAt: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 60 * 60 // 60mins
};
```

