TITLE: Creating Request Body for Swap Route Encoding
DESCRIPTION: Prepares the request body for the POST API call that encodes the swap route. It includes the route summary, sender and recipient addresses, and slippage tolerance to ensure the swap executes within acceptable boundaries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/kyberswap-aggregator/developer-guides/execute-a-swap-with-the-aggregator-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const requestBody = {
    routeSummary: routeSummary,
    sender: signerAddress,
    recipient: signerAddress,
    slippageTolerance: 10 //0.1%
}
```

