TITLE: Formatting Fill Order Request Body (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to format the request body for the `/read-ks/api/v1/encode/fill-order-to` API endpoint. It creates a `FillOrderBody` object, including the order ID, taking amount, threshold amount, target address (signer), and the operator signature. This formatted request body is essential for encoding the fill order data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/limit-order/developer-guides/fill-limit-order.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const requestBody: FillOrderBody = {
    orderId: Number(targetOrderId),
    takingAmount: takingAmount.toString(),
    thresholdAmount: '0',
    target: signerAddress,
    operatorSignature: operatorSignature[0].operatorSignature
};
```

