TITLE: Configuring API Parameters for Operator Signature (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures the API parameters required to request an operator signature for a specific order ID. It creates a `targetPathConfig` object with the chain ID and the target order ID as parameters.  This configuration will be used to send a request to `/read-partner/api/v1/orders/operator-signature` to get the signature needed for filling the order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/limit-order/developer-guides/fill-limit-order.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const targetPathConfig = {
    params: {
        chainId: ChainId.MATIC.toString(),
        orderIds: targetOrderId
    }
};
```

