TITLE: Defining BuildMigrateRouteRequest Message in Protobuf
DESCRIPTION: Defines the request structure for building a zap-migrate transaction. Includes fields for sender and recipient addresses, route data, deadline, source, and NFT burning option. Incorporates field validations for addresses and deadline.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kybernetwork/kyberswap-documentation.git/blob/main/kyberswap-solutions/kyberswap-zap-as-a-service/kyberswap-zap-as-a-service-zaas-api/zaas-grpc-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: protobuf
CODE:
```
message BuildMigrateRouteRequest {
  string sender = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.pattern = "^0x[0-9A-Za-z]{40}$"];
  string recipient = 2 [(buf.validate.field) = {
    string: {pattern: "^0x[0-9A-Za-z]{40}$"}
    ignore: IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED
  }];
  bytes route = 3;
  fixed32 deadline = 4 [(buf.validate.field).cel = {
    id: "deadline.gte_now"
    message: "deadline must be in the future"
    expression: "this == 0u || this > int(now)"
  }];
  string source = 5;
  bool burn_nft = 6;
}
```

